As of the 2020 United States census, Salamanca had a population of 5,929. The ethnic and racial makeup of the population was 69.3% White, 2.6% African-American, 18.6% Native American, 0.7% Asian, <0.1% Pacific Islander, 6.7% reporting two or more races, and 6.7% Hispanic or Latino of any race. 66.3% of the population was non-Hispanic white.<ref name="QF2020">{{Cite web|title=Quick Facts: Salamanca city, New York|url=https://www.census.gov/quickfacts/fact/table/salamancacitynewyork/PST045219|website=census.gov |access-date=October 4, 2021}}</ref>

